Nike Popoola Great Nigeria Insurance Plc has said it made a financial commitment to support the insurers’ umbrella body, Nigerian Insurers Association intervention fund in the COVID-19 fight. It said in a statement that the coronavirus pandemic marked an unprecedented time in modern history that would require the best of humanity to overcome. “The new coronavirus has claimed thousands of lives and spread to nearly every country in the world,” it stated. It stated that the NIA’s intervention fund aimed at raising funds from member companies of the association to support immediate and long-term relief and recovery in vulnerable communities, to curb the COVID-19 spread in the country. The Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer, Great Nigeria Insurance, Mrs Cecilia Osipitan, said that the company remained committed to supporting every effort at containing the spread of the virus. She said, “As a result of the exponential spread of COVID-19 pandemic around the world and increase in confirmed cases in Nigeria; it is very important that as a responsive corporate entity, GNI remains committed to supporting every effort of the Federal government and the insurance industry aimed at combating the COVID-19 scourge in Nigeria.” Copyright PUNCH.
